le of the public scholar in addressing issues relating to truth, justice, social repair, and genocide. Hinton asks: Can scholars who serve as expert witnesses effectively contribute to international atrocity crimes tribunals where the focus is on legal guilt as opposed to academic explanation? What does the answer to this question say more generally about academia and the public sphere? At a time when the world faces a multitude of challenges, the answers Hinton provides to such questions about public scholarship are urgent.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEvidence, ExpertzCambodia. 0aForensic anthropology. 0aTrials (Crimes against humanity)zCambodia. 0aTrials (Genocide)zCambodia. 4aAsian Studies. 4aLegal History & Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  apublic scholars in the courtroom, Nuon Chea, expert witness testimony in international criminal tribunal, public scholarship and expert witnesses.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075182608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501765711?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501765711423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501765711/original  a978-3-11-075182-6  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099455-1  EB